# Firebase Configuration
# Copy this file to .env if needed for local development.

# Note: API keys are no longer stored in Flutter app.
# All Gemini API calls now route through the backend server, which uses ADC (Application Default Credentials).
# This keeps the API key secure on the server side only.

# Note: Firebase configuration files are auto-generated locally by flutterfire CLI
# See FIREBASE_SETUP.md for setup instructions
